commit.message:
TPACKET_V[23]: continue even if mlock() fails

If mlock() fails don't bail out just only continue.

mlock()ing the mmap()ed memory is not strictly necessary. It it fails we
can continue without problems albeit suboptimally. This can occur e.g.
when running in systemd-nspawn container.

Signed-off-by: Vitezslav Samel <vitezslav@samel.cz>

TPACKET_V[23]: continue even if mlock() fails

If mlock() fails don't bail out just only continue.

mlock()ing the mmap()ed memory is not strictly necessary. It it fails we
can continue without problems albeit suboptimally. This can occur e.g.
when running in systemd-nspawn container.

commit.message:
packet capture: don't reuse socket for multiple receive functions

After we successfuly set up the capturing ring on acquired file
descriptor we must not reuse this fd to anything else. We must close it
in case of other error (e.g. mlock() fail) to signal the kernel to free
the ring structure on the fd.

Signed-off-by: Vitezslav Samel <vitezslav@samel.cz>

commit.message:
Makefile: protect mandatory compile flags in CFLAGS

Many users are used to define their own CFLAGS on make cmdline. But this
would hide our mandatory CFLAGS entries; fix this by putting mandatory
compile flags into IPTRAF_CFLAGS variable.
